  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1-1654014157947-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1-1654014157947-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1-1654014157947-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1-1654014157947-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1-1654014157947-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let’s get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>sausage meat</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to the pan with the <strong>bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span></strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654014163620-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654014163620-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654014163620-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654014163620-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654014163620-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>ravioli </strong>for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> ravioli</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654014167084-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654014167084-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654014167084-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654014167084-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654014167084-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>saffron</strong> with 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>saffron stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654014170727-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654014170727-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654014170727-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654014170727-x1000.jpg",
